<li id="cite_note-Coll-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Coll_5-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Coll_5-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Coll_5-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFColl2004" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Steve_Coll" title="Steve Coll">Coll, Steve</a> (2004). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/ghostwarssecreth00coll/page/46"><i>Ghost Wars: The Secret History of the CIA, Afghanistan, and Bin Laden, from the Soviet Invasion to September 10, 2001</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/Penguin_Group" title="Penguin Group">Penguin Group</a>. pp.&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/ghostwarssecreth00coll/page/46">46</a>, 593. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781594200076" title="Special:BookSources/9781594200076"><bdi>9781594200076</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Ghost+Wars%3A+The+Secret+History+of+the+CIA%2C+Afghanistan%2C+and+Bin+Laden%2C+from+the+Soviet+Invasion+to+September+10%2C+2001&amp;rft.pages=46%2C+593&amp;rft.pub=Penguin+Group&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.isbn=9781594200076&amp;rft.aulast=Coll&amp;rft.aufirst=Steve&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fghostwarssecreth00coll%2Fpage%2F46&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOperation+Cyclone" class="Z3988"></span> cf. <cite id="CITEREFBrzezinski1979" class="citation web cs1"><a href="/wiki/Zbigniew_Brzezinski" title="Zbigniew Brzezinski">Brzezinski, Zbigniew</a> (26 December 1979). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://nsarchive.gwu.edu/NSAEBB/NSAEBB396/docs/1979-12-26%20Brzezinski%20to%20Carter%20on%20Afghanistan.pdf">"Reflections on Soviet Intervention in Afghanistan"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">16 February</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Reflections+on+Soviet+Intervention+in+Afghanistan&amp;rft.date=1979-12-26&amp;rft.aulast=Brzezinski&amp;rft.aufirst=Zbigniew&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnsarchive.gwu.edu%2FNSAEBB%2FNSAEBB396%2Fdocs%2F1979-12-26%2520Brzezinski%2520to%2520Carter%2520on%2520Afghanistan.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOperation+Cyclone" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFPentz1988" class="citation web cs1">Pentz, Peter A. (1988). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://elibrary.law.psu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1081&amp;context=psilr">"The Mujahidin Middleman: Pakistan 's Role in the Afghan Crisis and the International Rule of NonIntervention"</a>. Penn State International Law Review.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+Mujahidin+Middleman%3A+Pakistan+%27s+Role+in+the+Afghan+Crisis+and+the+International+Rule+of+NonIntervention&amp;rft.pub=Penn+State+International+Law+Review&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.aulast=Pentz&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter+A.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Felibrary.law.psu.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D1081%26context%3Dpsilr&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AOperation+Cyclone" class="Z3988"></span></span>
